	  <h4 class="section-header">Overview</h4>
		  <p id="overview"><i>WebVision</i> is an open source web tool that provides a unified rendering engine for perceptual psychology and vision study. With <i>WebVision</i>, you can render monocular and binocular content in Virtual Reality, Augmented Reality and Mixed Reality headsets agnostics to the operating system. VR scenes rendered from this application are supported by the majority of modern web browsers. For more information on supported browsers visit this <span><a target="_blank" href="https://webvr.rocks/">link</a>.</span> </p>
 
			<p>This project was created in order to assist in the study of human psychology when viewing objects in VR as parameters such as lens distortion, image structure or refresh rates are modified.</p>
